2%3A1736277050000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-117034207%2Cimgsize-562115.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fus%2Fhes-not-wrong-elon-musk-backs-alleged-sex-trafficker-andrew-tates-bid-for-uk-prime-minister%2Farticleshow%2F117033961.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F117033961.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3EElon%20Musk%20supports%20Andrew%20Tate's%20bid%20for%20UK%20Prime%20Minister%20despite%20Tate's%20criminal%20allegations%20and%20controversial%20views.%20Musk's%20involvement%20in%20British%20politics%2C%20including%20criticisms%20of%20Labour%20leader%20Keir%20Starmer%20and%20backing%20far-right%20figures%2C%20has%20ignited%20debate.%20Conservative%20spokespersons%20criticize%20Musk's%20actions%20as%20dangerous%20and%20misinformed.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TOI%20World%20Desk%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fus%2Fhes-not-wrong-elon-musk-backs-alleged-sex-trafficker-andrew-tates-bid-for-uk-prime-minister%2Farticleshow%2F117033961.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia-indiatimes-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fus%2Fhes-not-wrong-elon-musk-backs-alleged-sex-trafficker-andrew-tates-bid-for-uk-prime-minister%2Famp_articleshow%2F117033961.cms%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fus%2Fhes-not-wrong-elon-musk-backs-alleged-sex-trafficker-andrew-tates-bid-for-uk-prime-minister%2Famp_articleshow%2F117033961.cms%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Anita%20Anand%20Might%20Replace%20Justin%20Trudeau%20As%20Canadian%20PM.%20All%20About%20Her%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Col%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EOn%20Monday%2C%20Justin%20Trudeau%20announced%20his%20resignation%20paving%20the%20way%20for%20a%20new%20leader%20to%20be%20elected%20by%20March%2024.%20Anita%20Anand%2C%20the%20Minister%20of%20Transport%20and%20Internal%20Trade%2C%20is%20a%20front%20runner%20to%20replace%20him.%20Others%20being%20considered%20are%20Dominic%20LeBlanc%2C%20Chrystia%20Freeland%2C%20Melanie%20Joly%2C%20Francois-Philippe%20Champagne%2C%20and%20Mark%20Carney.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EAnita%20Anand%20is%20a%20senior%20member%20of%20the%20Liberal%20Party%20of%20Canada.%20She%20has%20been%20a%20member%20of%20parliament%20since%202019%2C%20and%20has%20held%20several%20key%20portfolios%2C%20including%20Minister%20of%20Public%20Services%20and%20Procurement%2C%20Minister%20of%20National%20Defence%2C%20and%20President%20of%20the%20Treasury%20Board.%20She%20has%20been%20the%20Transport%20and%20Internal%20Trade%20Minister%20since%202024.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EBorn%20on%20May%2020%2C%201967%20in%20Kentville%2C%20Nova%20Scotia%20to%20doctor%20parents%20Saroj%20D%20Ram%20and%20SV%20Anand%2C%20who%20moved%20to%20Canada%20from%20India%20in%20the%20early%201960s%2C%20Ms%20Anand%20and%20her%20family%20had%20humble%20beginnings%20-%20which%20played%20a%20big%20part%20in%20her%20values%20and%20shaped%20her%20professional%20ethics%20right%20since%20she%20was%20a%20student.%20Anita%20Anand%20has%20two%20sisters%2C%20Gita%20and%20Sonia.%20In%201985%2C%20when%20she%20was%2018%2C%20Ms%20Anand%20moved%20to%20Ontario%20where%20she%20pursued%20an%20academic%20degree%20in%20political%20science.%20She%20then%20completed%20a%20Bachelor%20of%20Arts%20(Honours)%20in%20Jurisprudence%20from%20Oxford%20University.%20She%20followed%20that%20up%20with%20a%20bachelors%20and%20a%20masters%20degree%20in%20law%20from%20Dalhousie%20University%20and%20University%20of%20Toronto%20respectively.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EIn%20the%20initial%20stages%20of%20her%20professional%20life%2C%20Ms%20Anand%20took%20up%20various%20teaching%20assignments%2C%20including%20at%20the%20renowned%20Yale%20Law%20School.%20During%20her%20stint%20as%20a%20law%20professor%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Toronto%2C%20she%20held%20the%20JR%20Kimber%20Chair%20in%20investor%20protection%20and%20corporate%20governance.%20She%20later%20became%20the%20Associate%20Dean%20of%20the%20University%20of%20Toronto%20as%20well%20as%20the%20Director%20of%20Policy%20and%20Research%20at%20the%20Capital%20Markets%20Institute%20at%20the%20Rotman%20School%20of%20Management.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EIn%201995%2C%20Anita%20Anand%20married%20John%20Knowlton%2C%20a%20Canadian%20lawyer%20and%20business%20executive%20who%20she%20had%20met%20during%20her%20post%20graduation%20in%20law%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Toronto.%20They%20have%20four%20children.%20They%20have%20lived%20in%20Oakville%20for%20more%20than%2021%20years%20-%20from%201997%20to%201999%2C%20and%20again%20from%202005%20to%20the%20present%20day.%20She%20has%20represented%20Oakville%20in%20the%20House%20of%20Commons%20since%202019.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EAnita%20Anand's%20political%20career%20began%20when%20she%20stood%20for%20election%20from%20Oakville%20in%202019%20and%20became%20the%20member%20of%20parliament%20from%20the%20constituency.%20As%20Minister%20of%20Public%20Services%2C%20she%20played%20a%20critical%20role%20during%20the%20COVID-19%20pandemic.%20She%20played%20a%20pivotal%20role%20in%20negotiating%20better%20medical%20supplies%20for%20Canadians%2C%20including%20supply%20of%20oxygen%2C%20masks%20and%20PPE%20kits%2C%20vaccine%20supplies%2C%20and%20rapid%20antigen%20tests.%20Her%20role%20as%20public%20services%20minister%20was%20noteworthy%20and%20gained%20nationwide%20appreciation.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EIn%202021%2C%20she%20was%20given%20the%20charge%20of%20being%20Minister%20of%20National%20Defence.%20In%20her%20role%2C%20she%20brought%20about%20fundamental%20reforms%20to%20Canada's%20military.%20Her%20noteworthy%20contributions%20include%20reforms%20to%20address%20cases%20of%20sexual%20misconduct%20in%20the%20Canadian%20Armed%20Forces.%20She%20was%20also%20responsible%20to%20oversee%20Canada's%20military%20aid%20to%20Ukraine.%20A%20reshuffle%20of%20Justin%20Trudeau's%20cabinet%20saw%20her%20being%20posted%20to%20the%20Treasury%20department%2C%20where%20she%20worked%20to%20bring%20about%20greater%20transparency%20in%20the%20financial%20system.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EAs%20Minister%20of%20Transport%20for%20nearly%20a%20year%2C%20Ms%20Anand%20has%20overseen%20infrastructure%20projects%20across%20Canada%20to%20improve%20roads%2C%20highways%20and%20rail%20transport.%20Addressing%20climate%20change%20has%20been%20central%20to%20her%20vision%20for%20a%20clean%20and%20green%20transport%20sector%20in%20Canada.%20She%20has%20also%20given%20emphasis%20to%20safety%20across%20the%20transportation%20sector%20by%20bring%20in%20reforms.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EAnita%20Anand%20has%20also%20been%20a%20strong%20advocate%20of%20inclusiveness%20and%20gender%20equality.%20She%20has%20actively%20spoken%20in%20favour%20of%20LGBTQIA%2B%20rights%20and%20supported%20the%20outlook%20for%20diversity%20in%20Canada.%20Being%20a%20person%20of%20Indian%20descent%2C%20she%20herself%20has%20become%20a%20face%20of%20Canada's%20diverse%20political%20landscape.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EWhile%20Kim%20Campbell%20from%20the%20Progressive%20Conservative%20Party%20of%20Canada%20became%20the%20first%20and%20only%20woman%20prime%20minister%20of%20Canada%20in%201993%2C%20there%20has%20been%20no%20woman%20PM%20from%20the%20Liberal%20Party.%20Should%20Anita%20Anand%20be%20selected%20as%20Justin%20Trudeau's%20replacement%2C%20she%20will%20create%20history%20by%20becoming%20the%20first%20woman%20of%20colour%20and%20first%20Canadian%20of%20Indian%20origin%20to%20become%20the%20prime%20minister%20of%20Canada.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fol%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1736275860000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2025-01%2Fmhhq75a4_anita-anand-justin-trudeau-twitter_625x300_07_January_25.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-n