%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2025-01%2Fko0813f8_kinmen-island-taiwan_625x300_07_January_25.jpg%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2025-01%2Fcjoqic44_matsu-island-taiwan_625x300_07_January_25.jpg%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDespite%20being%20right%20on%20the%20coastline%20with%20mainland%20China%2C%20it%20is%20interesting%20to%20note%20that%20Beijing%20has%20never%20been%20able%20to%20take%20over%20these%20Taiwanese%20islands%20in%20battle.%20In%20fact%2C%20China%20has%20lost%20two%20battles%20decisively%20to%20Taiwan.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EPRC%20vs%20ROC%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChina%20and%20Taiwan%20are%20separated%20by%20the%20Strait%20of%20Taiwan%20-%20a%20waterway%20that%20connects%20the%20South%20China%20Sea%20to%20the%20East%20China%20Sea%20between%20the%20two%20nations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBefore%201949%2C%20China%20was%20known%20as%20the%20Republic%20of%20China%20and%20was%20founded%20on%20the%20ideology%20of%20democratic%20values.%20It%20was%20led%20by%20the%20Kuomintang%20Party%2C%20founded%20in%201912%20and%20advocated%20by%20its%20founder%20and%20ideologue%20Sun%20Yat-sen%2C%20who%20organised%20the%20party%20on%20a%20values%20of%20democratic%20centralism.%20Years%20later%2C%20during%20the%20civil%20war%20with%20communist%20forces%20led%20by%20Mao%20Zedong%2C%20the%20Kuomintang%20was%20led%20by%20Chiang%20Kai-shek%2C%20a%20co-founder%20of%20the%20party%20and%20then%20President%20of%20the%20Republic%20of%20China.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Chinese%20civil%20war%20ended%20in%201949%20with%20a%20victory%20of%20Mao%20Zedong's%20communist%20movement%20and%20defeat%20of%20Chiang%20Kai-shek's%20ruling%20Kuomintang%20party%2C%20which%20had%20to%20flee%20to%20Taiwan.%20Mao%20Zedong%20declared%20that%20the%20Republic%20of%20China%20will%20henceforth%20be%20known%20to%20the%20world%20as%20People's%20Republic%20of%20China%20-%20a%20communist%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Kuomintang%20and%20its%20democratic%20ideals%20took%20shelter%20in%20the%20island%20nation%20of%20Taiwan%2C%20whose%20official%20name%20is%20still%20the%20Republic%20of%20China%20-%20a%20democratic%20nation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20the%20way%20it%20has%20remained%20for%20the%20last%2076%20years%2C%20despite%20multiple%20attempts%20by%20communist%20forces%20to%20decimate%20democracy%20and%20wipe%20out%20its%20ideals%20from%20Taiwan%20and%20its%20territories%20-%20all%20of%20which%20have%20failed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChina%2C%20now%20considered%20a%20global%20superpower%2C%20still%20aims%20to%20make%20Taiwan%20its%20own%2C%20and%20Xi%20Jinping%2C%20who%20currently%20leads%20the%20Chinese%20Communist%20Party%20desires%20to%20fulfill%20what%20Mao%20Zedong%20couldn't.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ETHE%20BATTLE%20OF%20KINMEN%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETowards%20the%20end%20of%20the%20civil%20war%2C%20when%20victory%20over%20Mainland%20China%20was%20certain%2C%20Mao%20Zedong's%20Communist%20Party%20decided%20to%20launch%20a%20crushing%20offensive%20against%20Taiwan%20-%20the%20final%20frontier%20yet%20to%20be%20conquered.%20So%20fervent%20their%20hatred%20for%20the%20Kuomintang%20and%20its%20democratic%20ideals%20that%20the%20Communist%20Party%20wanted%20to%20eradicate%20every%20square%20inch%20of%20the%20Republic%20of%20China.%20Beijing's%20stance%20to%20take%20over%20Taiwan%20%26quot%3Bat%20all%20cost%26quot%3B%20stems%20from%20the%20policy%20that%20as%20long%20as%20there%20is%20a%20Republic%20of%20China%2C%20there%20is%20a%20chink%20in%20the%20armour%2C%20from%20where%20an%20uprising%2C%20a%20civil%20war%20or%20the%20spread%20of%20another%20ideology%20is%20possible.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETaking%20over%20Taiwan%20would%20mean%20leaving%20the%20mainland%20and%20sending%20troops%20overseas%20to%20the%20island%20nation%20and%20going%20to%20war%20with%20them%20in%20their%20own%20territory%20-%20a%20move%20that%20would%20not%20be%20easy.%20Mao%20Zedong%20decided%20that%20to%20finally%20take%20over%20Taiwan%2C%20it%20is%20a%20must%20to%20first%20take%20over%20is%20islets%20and%20territories%20which%20are%20located%20closer%20to%20the%20mainland%20-%20namely%20the%20Kinmen%20and%20Matsu.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKinmen%20consists%20of%20two%20large%20islands%20and%20thirteen%20islets.%20Being%20the%20closer%20of%20the%20two%20Taiwanese%20territories%2C%20Mao%20Zedong%20decided%20to%20target%20these%20first.%20Greater%20Kinmen%20-%20the%20largest%20island%20-%20became%20the%20primary%20target.%20But%20its%20geography%20was%20an%20advantage%20to%20the%20Taiwanese%20forces.%20Its%20eastern%20side%20has%20mountainous%20terrain%20and%20its%20coastline%20rocky%20and%20rugged%20makes%20it%20a%20challenge%20for%20an%20external%20threat.%20its%20western%20side%2C%20facing%20mainland%20China%20has%20beaches%20which%20are%20easier%20for%20an%20enemy%20to%20breach%20in%20times%20of%20war%20-%20and%20for%20Beijing%20logistically%20suitable%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Chinese%20Army%20decided%20to%20do%20this%20in%20two%20bursts%20-%20the%20first%20comprising%20roughly%2010%2C000%20soldiers%20who%20would%20reach%20the%20island%20and%20set%20up%20a%20garrison%2C%20then%20wait%20for%20reinforcements%20to%20arrive%20-%20another%2010%2C000%20soldiers.%20This%20they%20thought%20would%20be%20enough%20to%20overpower%20the%20Taiwanese%20forces%2C%20which%20were%20estimated%20to%20be%20of%20a%20similar%20strength%20in%20numbers.%20China%20assumed%20that%20the%20Taiwanese%20forces%20would%20be%20demoralised%20with%20the%20fall%20of%20mainland%20China%20and%20would%20be%20easy%20to%20defeat.%20But%20that%20wasn't%20to%20be.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnticipating%20such%20a%20move%20by%20communist%20China%2C%20Taiwanese%20forces%20had%20lined%20up%20the%20coastline%20with%20nearly%207%2C500%20landmines.%20The%20beaches%20were%20secured%20to%20stop%20any%20form%20of%20amphibious%20transport%20and%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20island%20was%20fortified%20with%20strategically%20placed%20mines%2C%20traps%2C%20and%20hundreds%20of%20bunkers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETaiwan%20had%20also%20prepared%20well%20for%20such%20an%20attack%20by%20strengthening%20its%20infantry%20as%20well%20as%20its%20armoured%20divisions%2C%20including%20two%20tank%20regiments.%20The%20battle%20began%20on%20October%2025%2C%20with%20China%20aiming%20to%20wrest%20control%20of%20the%20island%20in%20three%20days.%20So%20began%20the%20Battle%20of%20Kimen%2C%20which%20is%20officially%20known%20as%20the%20Battle%20of%20Guningtou.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20land%20mines%20and%20traps%20led%20to%20heavy%20Chinese%20casualties%20and%20the%20armoured%20divisions%20of%20the%20Taiwanese%20forces%20gave%20a%20crushing%20blow%20to%20the%20Chinese%20troops.%20The%20amphibious%20transport%20vessels%20were%20damaged%20by%20anti-amphibious%20weapons%20and%20ended%20up%20being%20beached%20on%20the%20island.%20Their%20failure%20to%20return%20to%20the%20mainland%20meant%20that%20the%20next%20round%20of%20soldiers%20could%20not%20be%20sent%20in%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20artillery%20firing%20from%20mainland%20China%20did%20not%20help%20much.%20Meanwhile%20the%20Taiwanese%20air%20force%20and%20navy%20began%20a%20counter-offense%20by%20first%20damaging%20all%20the%20Chinese%20boats%20near%20the%20Kinmen%20islands.%20Soldiers%20of%20the%20Chinese%20Army%20faced%20heavy%20casualties%20against%20the%20US-made%20machine%20guns%20and%20tanks%20which%20the%20Taiwanese%20soldiers%20used.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20end%20of%20day%20one%20itself%2C%20the%20Chinese%20army%20lost%20more%20than%20half%20its%20soldiers%20and%20more%20than%2070%20per%20cent%20of%20its%20ammunition%20and%20transport.%20with%20its%20boats%20and%20amphibious%20vessels%20destroyed%2C%20the%20troops%20were%20isolated.%20The%20Taiwanese%20military%20also%20further%20strengthened%20its%20positions%20by%20vastly%20cutting%20off%20Guningtou.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20next%20day%20reinforcements%20managed%20to%20reach%20with%20approximately%201%2C000%20Chinese%20soldiers%20joining%20the%20battle.%20But%20by%20then%20the%20Taiwanese%20were%20on%20the%20offense%20and%20with%20US-made%20M5A1%20Suart%20light%20tanks%20aiding%20the%20infantry%2C%20took%20control%20of%20Guningtou%2C%20which%20was%20under%20communist%20control%20at%20the%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBy%20the%20end%20of%20day%20two%2C%20the%20Chinese%20troops%20ran%20out%20of%20food%20and%20supplies.%20The%20following%20morning%20Taiwanese%20soldiers%20overpowered%20the%20communist%20forces%20and%20more%20than%205%2C000%20soldiers%20were%20kept%20as%20prisoners%20of%20war.%20Not%20only%20was%20Kinmen%20retained%20by%20Taiwan%2C%20but%20the%20communist%20forces%20lost%20the%20control%20of%20Guningtou%20too.%20It%20was%20a%20humiliating%20defeat%20for%20Mao%20Zedong%20and%20People's%20Republic%20of%20China%20-%20a%20name%20declared%20just%20earlier%20that%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThroughout%20the%201950s%20and%20beyond%2C%20multiple%20invasions%20were%20attempted%20by%20China%2C%20but%20each%20attempt%20failed.%20The%20United%20States%20has%20on%20several%20occasions%20come%20to%20the%20aid%20of%20Taiwan%20as%20China's%20influence%20grew%2C%20but%20China%20never%20dared%20attack%20the%20US%20navy%20directly%20as%20Beijing%20did%20not%20want%20direct%20war%20with%20Washington.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEven%20today%2C%20China%20considers%20Taiwan%20a%20renegade%20island%20province%20-%20one%20that%20it%20must%20take%20over%20%26quot%3Bat%20all%20costs%26quot%3B.%20Beijing%20has%20repeatedly%20said%20it%20will%20not%20renounce%20the%20use%20of%20force%20to%20bring%20Taiwan%20under%20its%20control.%20Its%20war%20drills%20are%20increasing%20in%20scale%20and%20frequency%20with%20the%20latest%20manoeuvres%20as%20recently%20as%20New%20Year's%20day.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1736263620000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2025-01%2F27su9i5o_battle-of-kinmen-chinese-prisoners-of-war-taken-by-taiwan_625x300_07_January_25.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fwhen-taiwan-crushed-china-in-battle-taking-over-5-000-prisoners-of-war-7421733%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22In%20his%20New%20Year%20speech%2C%20Chinese%20President%20Xi%20Jinping%20threatened%20that%20%26quot%3Bno%20one%20can%20stop%20the%20reunification%26quot%3B%20of%20Taiwan%20with%20China.%20As%20Xi%20Jinping%20delivered%20his%20speech%2C%20the%20People's%20Liberation%20Army%20Navy%20conducted%20military%20drills%20to%20show%20its%20might%20to%20Taiwan%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fwhen-taiwan-crushed-china-in-battle-taking-over-5-000-prisoners-of-war-7421733%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22A%20tribute%3A%20'Manmohan%20Singh%20was%20unfailingly%20measured%2C%20thoughtful%20and%20wise'%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1736263565000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Findia-news%2Fa-tribute-manmohan-singh-was-unfailingly-measured-thoughtful-and-wise-125010701231_1.html%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Knowing%20Manmohan%20was%20one%20of%20the%20greatest%20privileges%20of%20my%20life.%20He%20showed%20me%20and%20everybody%20else%20what%20leadership%20and%20service%20truly%20mean%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Findia-news%2Fa-tribute-manmohan-singh-was-unfailingly-measured-thoughtful-and-wise-125010701231_1.html%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A